        "JR Kyushu's profit jump came from three reinforcing sources. First, railway ridership recovered on the return of travel and an inbound-tourism boom into Kyushu's cities and resorts. Second, the 2025 fare and charge revision lifted the revenue earned per passenger. Third, its real-estate and hotel businesses — a deliberately large part of the group — kept growing as people returned to its station-side developments. Together these drove operating profit up over 25%. In short: a recovering railway, higher fares, and a thriving property-and-hotel arm combined to produce sharply higher profit.",
