        "Hankyu Hanshin Holdings (9042) is Kansai's largest private-railway group, built around the two famous lines that give it its name — Hankyu and Hanshin. But it is far more than trains: it is one of Japan's strongest urban real-estate developers (its Umeda district in central Osaka is a crown jewel), it runs hotels and travel, and it owns entertainment assets including the Hanshin Tigers baseball team and the Takarazuka Revue. So it combines a dense commuter-rail backbone with prime city property and a big entertainment arm. Simply put: it moves Osaka and Kobe, and it owns much of the most valuable land and many of the biggest attractions they sit on.",
