        "Revenue and profit dipped modestly because this small Hyogo regional railway saw only limited passenger recovery while its operating costs rose. Unlike the larger Kansai majors, it does not sit on the main inbound-tourism arteries or capture much direct upside from the 2025 Osaka-Kansai Expo, so the powerful tailwinds lifting its bigger peers largely passed it by. There was no shock here — just a quiet, modest softening at a small regional operator. In short: limited passenger recovery plus higher costs, and little of the inbound/Expo boost that helped the bigger Kansai railways.",
