        "Tobu Railway (9001) is one of the Tokyo area's largest private railways, with a sprawling network reaching north and east from the capital into Saitama, Tochigi and Gunma. Beyond trains it is a diversified group: it develops and rents real estate, runs hotels and leisure businesses, and owns landmark attractions including Tokyo Skytree — the broadcasting tower that is one of Tokyo's biggest tourist draws. Simply put: Tobu both carries commuters and tourists across the northern Kanto region and owns the property and attractions, including Skytree, that they visit.",
