        "Fukuyama Transporting (9075) is one of Japan's largest less-than-truckload (LTL) freight carriers — the kind of trucking where many different customers' small shipments are consolidated onto one truck and sorted through a national network of terminals. Founded in Hiroshima in 1948, 'Fukutsu' moves business-to-business cargo (parts, goods, documents) across the country on its own trucks and depots, rather than home-parcel delivery. Because it owns the trucks and employs the drivers, its profit depends heavily on what it can charge per shipment versus what it pays for fuel, labour and drivers. Simply put: a nationwide B2B trucking network whose margins live or die on freight rates minus driver and fuel costs.",
